Person.comment:
Ron Caspi received his PhD in Marine Microbiology in 1996 from the Scripps Institution of Oceanography in La Jolla, CA, under the guidance of Dr. Bradley Tebo and Dr. Margo Haygood. He completed his post-graduate education in 1999 with Dr. Donald Helinski at the Center for Molecular Genetics at UC San Diego.

After three years with Pangene Corporation, where he managed the automation and bioinformatics department, Ron joined SRI International in 2004, and has been the head curator of the MetaCyc database ever since.

Protein.comment:
EC 1.6.2.4, NADPH—hemoprotein reductase, is a flavoprotein containing both FMN and FAD that catalyzes the reduction of cytochrome P-450 enzymes, such as EC 1.14.14.1, unspecific monooxygenase and EC 1.14.14.16, steroid 21-monooxygenase.

The enzyme also catalyzes the reduction of EC 1.14.14.18, heme oxygenase (biliverdin-producing), and can reduce cytochrome b5 and cytochrome c.

The structure shown here shows the reduced form of the flavin cofactor.
